## Quick Q&A Prep

| Likely Question | Key Answer |
|----------------|------------|
| **Why RAG instead of fine-tuning?** | RAG lets me ground responses in a specific financial guide without expensive fine-tuning. The knowledge base can be updated by just swapping the [.txt](file:///c:/Programs/01_Projects/Projects/04_FinFriend/requirements.txt) file — no retraining needed. |
| **Why HuggingFace embeddings instead of Gemini embeddings?** | `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` is FREE, runs locally, and produces high-quality 384-dim embeddings. Avoids API cost for the embedding step — only the LLM calls use the paid Gemini API. |
| **Why FAISS over Pinecone/ChromaDB?** | FAISS is lightweight, fast, runs locally with no cloud dependency, and perfect for a single-document knowledge base. No need for a managed vector DB at this scale. |
| **How does the dynamic query generation help?** | Instead of embedding the user's raw data for retrieval (which would be a poor semantic match), I use an LLM to generate a focused search query. E.g., for a user with high debt, it generates "how to manage high-interest debt on low salary" — much better retrieval quality. |
| **How do you handle auth/API key security?** | API key stored in [.env](file:///c:/Programs/01_Projects/Projects/04_FinFriend/.env) file (local) and Streamlit Secrets (production). Never committed to Git. Accessed via `os.getenv()`. |
| **What's the biggest challenge?** | Designing the RAG pipeline so the 3 chained LLM calls work cohesively — the dynamic query had to be specific enough for good retrieval but not so narrow that it missed relevant context. Also managing `useEffect`-equivalent state transitions in Streamlit's re-run model. |
| **Why Streamlit over React?** | Streamlit is purpose-built for data/AI apps — built-in chat UI, session state, caching, and one-click deployment. For an LLM chatbot, it's the fastest path to production without building a separate frontend. |
| **How does the follow-up Q&A work?** | Each follow-up question triggers a new FAISS retrieval for fresh context, combined with the full chat history. This lets the bot answer new topics while remembering the entire conversation. |
| **What's the knowledge base?** | A 70K+ character, 390-line comprehensive financial guide covering Indian-specific topics: 50/30/20 rule, debt avalanche/snowball, EPF/PPF/NPS, SIPs, and real advice from r/IndiaInvestments. |
| **How would you scale this?** | Add PDF/multi-doc support, switch to a managed vector DB (Pinecone), add user authentication to save sessions, integrate data visualization (Altair charts) for the financial report. |
